# dev-workflow transition table (composable state machine).
#
# Directives:
#   @initial  <state>      the start state
#   @terminal <state>      a terminal state (no outgoing transitions)
#   @gate     <state>      a human-gate state: leaving it (any event except
#                          `exit`) requires a prior `workflow.sh approve`
#   @worker   <state>      a work-state run in a fresh process: `workflow.sh work`
#                          executes workers/<state>.txt via `claude -p`. The
#                          orchestrator must delegate, not do the work inline.
#
# Transitions (one per line):
#   <from> <event> <to> [counter=NAME max=N] [gate=1]
#     counter/max : bounded loop guard. The event is allowed only while the
#                   named attempt counter < max; firing it increments the counter.
#                   Counters with the same NAME are shared across transitions.
#     gate=1      : firing this event requires prior `workflow.sh approve`
#                   (human sign-off). Resets after firing.
#
# `exit` is always available from any non-terminal state and goes to `exited`.
# Every non-terminal state should have a prompt at nodes/<state>.md
# (the `-` in a state name maps to `nodes/<state>.md`, e.g. plan-approve -> nodes/plan-approve.md).
#
# Edit this table to recompose the workflow; the workflow-retro skill may rewrite it.

@initial  plan
@terminal done
@terminal exited
@gate     plan-approve
@worker   plan
@worker   implement
@worker   validate
@worker   minor-fix
@worker   recheck
@worker   open-pr

plan          submit    plan-approve
plan-approve  revise    plan
plan-approve  resume    implement
implement     submit    validate
validate      rework    implement     counter=rework max=5
validate      minor     minor-fix
validate      recheck   recheck
minor-fix     rework    implement     counter=rework max=5
minor-fix     recheck   recheck
recheck       continue  implement     counter=continue max=1
recheck       pr        open-pr
open-pr       submit    followup
followup      submit    done
